      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(mattermost): backfill thread history from server when in-memory window is empty",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where Mattermost users replying in an existing thread could lose earlier thread context after the OpenClaw monitor restarted or the agent session was reset.\n\nFixes #93204\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe Mattermost monitor now backfills a cold local thread-history window from the Mattermost thread endpoint before building inbound context. The backfill marker is keyed by the stored agent `sessionId`, not the stable route session key, so a real `/new` or session reset gets its own recovery fetch while same-session follow-ups avoid repeated server fetches.\n\n## User Impact\n\nMattermost thread replies keep useful prior context after restart or `/new`, without adding repeated thread-history requests to normal same-session follow-ups.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.inbound-system-event.test.ts extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.test.ts`: 72 passed; covers stable `route.sessionKey`, stored `sessionId` rotation, same-session no-refetch, and reset-session refetch.\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test`: passed.\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.ts extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.test.ts extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.inbound-system-event.test.ts`: passed.\n- `git diff --check`: passed.\n\nLive proof: local Docker Mattermost Team Edition 10.11.21 at `http://localhost:8065`, with tokens and Mattermost ids redacted. The proof used real Mattermost REST auth, posts, and `/api/v4/posts/<root>/thread` through `monitorMattermostProvider`; a fake websocket only injected `posted` events into the monitor. The route/thread session key stayed stable while the stored agent `sessionId` rotated. Cold start included prior root/thread context, same-session server-only context stayed absent, and stored-session reset included new server-only prior context:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mattermost\": \"10.11.21 local Docker, token/id redacted\",\n  \"routeSessionKey\": \"stable, redacted\",\n  \"threadSessionKeyStable\": true,\n  \"storedSessionIds\": [\n    \"stored-session-before-reset\",\n    \"stored-session-after-reset\"\n  ],\n  \"dispatchCount\": 3,\n  \"firstColdStartContainsPriorThreadContext\": true,\n  \"firstColdStartContainsRootContext\": true,\n  \"sameSessionSkippedServerOnlyContext\": true,\n  \"storedSessionIdResetContainsNewPriorContext\": true\n}\n```\n\nAI-assisted: built with Codex\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93204-Mattermost--thread-context-los",
